---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Docs"
  description="Documentation entry point for CodeArmy."
>
  <section class="container page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Docs</p>
    <h1>Start with the quick narrative, then deepen the product story.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      The first public docs set should stay small and clear: what CodeArmy is, why it exists, and
      how to start shaping it into a product.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a class="button" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}docs/quickstart/`}>Open Quickstart</a>
      <a class="button-secondary" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}how-it-works/`}>
        Read How It Works
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
